License: CC0-1.0
License File: LICENSE
Security Critical: no
Shipped: no

Description:
A representative subset of test images from the jpegsuite project, which
provides a collection of JPEG images for testing JPEG decoders. Inspired by
PngSuite. Only the generated JPEG image files are included here (CC0 licensed);
the generator code (GPL v3) is not included.

Files are selected from all 7 upstream directories using a test matrix approach
to maximize coverage while minimizing redundancy:
- Size/extreme/marker features tested once in baseline (encoding-independent).
- Core color/interleaving/subsampling tested per DCT encoding mode.
- Progressive scan variations tested in both Huffman and arithmetic modes.
- Lossless predictor and bit-depth variants tested in lossless_huffman.

Directory layout (matches upstream names):
- baseline/: Baseline DCT (SOF0) 8-bit images (24 files)
- extended_huffman/: Extended Huffman DCT (SOF1) 8-bit + 12-bit (15 files)
- extended_arithmetic/: Extended arithmetic DCT (SOF9) 8-bit (5 files)
- progressive_huffman/: Progressive Huffman DCT (SOF2) 8-bit + 12-bit (21 files)
- progressive_arithmetic/: Progressive arithmetic DCT (SOF10) 8-bit (9 files)
- lossless_huffman/: Lossless Huffman (SOF3) 8-bit + 16-bit (6 files)
- lossless_arithmetic/: Lossless arithmetic (SOF11) 8-bit (3 files)

Total: 83 files (from ~296 upstream).

Local Modifications:
- Only a representative subset of the upstream images is included. See the plan
  in the test code for the full test matrix rationale.
- Each test entry has an `expect_failure` flag set empirically based on whether
  Chromium's libjpeg-turbo build can decode the file.
